rComments: Worst lab to take. Sure you will learn a couple of things in the long run but it is not the great lab experience you are looking for. First of all organization 0/10 you open brightspace just to be lost. Grading scale is the worst. A lot of high expectations with barely any instructions and all your knowledge is googling on your own time so have fun

Dr. Oran is great. I don't really understand all these bad reviews since the course is quite easy because his expectations are clear! Get ready to participate in the Journal Clubs and to do a bunch of homeworks every week. Dr. Oran is direct but really accessible, don't hesitate to go at his office hours.

Genuinely my favourite prof + class. He seriously cares about you learning the material. It is not an easy class but it is extremely rewarding. You walk out the class with applicable skills for after grad. He is easy to talk to and is always there to help you. Will recommend him over and over again

One of the few science professors at uOttawa who cares about students learning instead of chasing a grade distribution. His teaching is better if you're more of a conceptual learner and not someone who memorizes. He also encourages discussion and is very approachable.

Bad prof in general. means well but some of his questions do not reflect what this lab should be about. Teaches us stuff from 1st year like we have never seen that before. Beware: if you take it in french, his translation arent good. Demand a bilingual exam AT ALL COST.

I don't know where to start with how this class is structured. He speeds through 60 pages of in-depth textbook material in 15 minute lectures filled with figures with little to no explanation. To put it simply, he teaches the course like its trivial review (it's not) and his testing is a whole other review. AVOID!!!

He's a nice guy, but he talks very fast and often goes off on tangents that seem relevant until later he says that you don't need to know anything he just said. The expectations for the exams are super unclear and the exam questions are very strange (eg Bob Dylan's song lyrics say "..." what type of differentiation is he?). Take a different course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This was one of my favourite labs out of the ones ive taken. Dr. Oran is clear about his expectations although they seem tough i believe the grading is fair. You will actually learn good techniques in this lab and will understand research through journal clubs.
extremely disorganized, never gives good feedback and rude

The worst professor I have ever seen in the whole university year. He is really rude to approach and condescending. I regret taking this course with him. I just hate how he talks so aggressively. Please avoid future students

By far the worst prof I've had in my four years of university. He's a nice enough guy but I have never been in such a disorganized class and he talks crazy fast. Learning ends up being really self-directed and even still the exams are hard. Don't take this course if you don't have to.

He's a really nice guy, but man does he get off topic. He's soo disorganized and his lectures were all over the place. His powerpoints are mostly images and its really hard to understand his explanations and thought process. The concent is very interesting and his marking is very fair (part marks on multiple choice). Midterms are hard!

The only thing going for him is that he's attractive.. but don't be fooled. Midterm average was less than 50% even after the bell curve.. the final was worse even with a freebee question. The course was 90% learning technical skills & the reasoning behind each lab, which were not tested on the final at large. Most of the final was on the 10%.. smh

Yeah, the other reviews are not super clear. Above average by recording his lectures (redoes them if they are crappy too). Tests are hard but he is VERY flexible with grading ; part-marks for multiple choice questions... no complaints there! But you need to take good notes and if you have a question, he answered me quickly and clearly.

Great Prof. Great course. It is designed to teach you new skills that you will carry your whole career. Prof. Oran is very helpful - make use of the office hours. His exams are not difficult but tricky. He is testing your ability to solve problems not your memorization skills. I recommend it to everyone who is interested in cell bio.

Extremely interesting class and a great prof! GO TO CLASS, take good notes and ask questions. Midterms and exam are very fair, but contain tricky multiple choice so take your time and don't rush. Honestly my favourite class so far. I learned so much new stuff that is actually relevant to other courses and to real life. Highly recommended!

You can do really well in this class if you're willing to put in the effort to learn. Read the text, GO TO HIS OFFICE! he is VERY helpful, and definitely definitely attend class. His slides have limited words, but his lectures will go over any info for tests. Very interesting class, probably the most interested 300 level BIO course

Either you like him, either you don’t. I really enjoyed his class and I learned a lot. You have to be ready to put in the efforts and the exams are hard. It is not an easy A class, but you can learn a lot of useful tips that will serve in your science carrier.

He is definitely a tough professor, so if you don't want to work hard to really learn then you should probably avoid his classes. That being said, I learned more in his classes than I have in all of university. Go to his office hours!! He will help you and you will definitely benefit from it. He will teach you vital knowledge for an science student

I agree, he is a tough professor. But, he is one of the best professors ottawaU. Get to know him & you wont regret it. I had him for 3 classes in one year, and he has taught me more than any other professor has at this school, he knows his stuff & has an open door policy for a reason! Make sure you do ANY readings he suggests! and i mean ANY.
interesting course.  Like the videos but the exams are tough.  If you are looking for an easy A, this is not the course to take.  But the material is interesting...

The exams were brutal! He would put slides up and say "this one is important" and would spend maybe a minute discussing it. I remember someone saying "So what was so important about that slide?". You need to attend class because his slides are not self explanatory. you need to print out the notes. Write fast. good luck!
The course is really interesting. You have to show up to class otherwise textbook is impossible.  He answered my questions though when I saw him.  I liked the videos and case studies.

Agreed. Horrifying exams....and he does not seem to even consider bell curving or makes it any easier..midterms and final exam got harder and harder. Does it make you happy to fail half the class or see straight A students getting B or C? God, we need a good transcript. stop ruining our future.

Worst prof I've had in 4 years of university. His exams reflect useless information that he mentions in class then tells you that you don't have to know. Be ready to memorize all of the slides and "what they mean". Not organized and makes a lot of mistakes while he teaches. Worst experience ever.
HOrrible prof with ridiculous exams. good luck
